nt is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Margarita De Andria was born about 1245, in Italy. She had at least 1 daughter with d’Andria."},"et":{"about 1245–":"umbes 1245–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","Abt 1256":"umbes 1256","1245":"1245","1256":"1256","1240":"1240","about 1245":"umbes 1245","1291":"1291","Italy":"Itaalia","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1245–":"noin 1245–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","Abt 1256":"noin 1256","1245":"1245","1256":"1256","1240":"1240","about 1245":"noin 1245","1291":"1291","Italy":"Italia","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1245–":"environ 1245–Décédée","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1245–Female":"1245–Décédée","Abt 1256":"environ 1256","1245":"1245","1256":"1256","1240":"1240","about 1245":"environ 1245","1291":"1291","Italy":"Italie","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Margarita De Andria est née environ 1245, à Italie. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec d’Andria."},"de":{"about 1245–":"um 1245–Verstorben","1240–Male":"1240–Verstorben","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1245–Female":"1245–Verstorben","Abt 1256":"um 1256","1245":"1245","1256":"1256","1240":"1240","about 1245":"um 1245","1291":"1291","Italy":"Italien","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Margarita De Andria wurde um 1245 in Italien geboren. Sie hatte mit d’Andria mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1245–":"about 1245–Desede","1240–Male":"1240–Desede","1256–1291":"125